    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-02-16T12:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-02-16T12:00:00-05:00" n="138"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                <head>138. Minutes of a National Security Council Review Group Meeting<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d138fn1">Source: National Archives, Nixon Presidential
                        Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Files, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Institutional Files (H-Files), Box H–111,
                        Senior Review Group, <gloss target="#t_SRG_1">SRG</gloss> Minutes Originals
                        1970. Secret. The meeting took place in the White House Situation
                        Room.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            from="1970-02-16T12:00:00-05:00" to="1970-02-16T12:45:00-05:00">February
                            16, 1970, noon–12:45 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>U.S. Policy Toward Post-De Gaulle France (<gloss target="#t_NSSM_1"
                            >NSSM</gloss> 60)<note n="2" xml:id="d138fn2">
                            <ref target="#d130">Document 130</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPATION</head>
                    <item>Chairman—<persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">State</hi>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HMJ_1">Martin J. Hillenbrand</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWI_1">William I. Cargo</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Donald McHenry</item>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Defense</hi>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_NGW_1">G. Warren Nutter</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <gloss target="#t_CIA_1">CIA</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </item>
                    <item>R. <persName corresp="#p_SJL_1">Jack Smith</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <gloss target="#t_JCS_1">JCS</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </item>
                    <item>LTG F. T. Unger</item>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <gloss target="#t_OEP_1">OEP</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </item>
                    <item>Haakon Lindjord</item>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <gloss target="#t_USIA_1">USIA</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </item>
                    <item>Frank Shakespeare</item>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Staff</hi>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SH_2">Helmut Sonnenfeldt</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>William Hyland</item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KRT_1">Richard T. Kennedy</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJW_1">Jeanne W. Davis</persName>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p rend="center">SUMMARY OF DECISIONS</p>
                <p>The Issues Paper<note n="3" xml:id="d138fn3">See <ref target="#d134fn1">footnote
                            1, Document 134</ref>.</note> should be revised to:</p>
                <p>a. discuss French entry into the <gloss target="#t_NPG_1">NPG</gloss> in terms of
                    its advantages and disadvantages and to absorb Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_RWP_1">Rogers</persName>’ recommendations;</p>
                <p>b. add a sub-option on the joint targeting issue allowing for tripartite
                        US–<gloss target="#t_UK_1">UK</gloss> French talks with <gloss
                        target="#t_SACEUR_1">SACEUR</gloss> “being kept informed” with an indication
                    that it is the least desirable option.</p>
                <p>—In the light of the information that the French did not plan to raise military
                    issues during the <persName corresp="#p_PG_1">Pompidou</persName> visit the
                    President should be asked if he still wishes an <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"
                        >NSC</gloss> meeting prior to the visit.</p>
                <p>—That the question of the proposed French Mediterranean strategy be raised at the
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> meeting if it takes place.<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d138fn4">See <ref target="#d140">Document 140</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>—That, of the military issues, the US raise with <persName corresp="#p_PG_1"
                        >Pompidou</persName> only the question of association with the <gloss
                        target="#t_NPG_1">NPG</gloss>.<note n="5" xml:id="d138fn5">The revised paper
                        was completed on February 18. (National Archives, Nixon Presidential
                        Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Files, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Institutional Files (H-Files), Box H–153,
                        National Security Study Memoranda, <gloss target="#t_NSSM_1">NSSM</gloss>
                        60)</note>
                </p>
                <p>[Omitted here is the discussion.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
